Boil the @water{400%ml}. Peel and cut the @red onion{1} in half lengthways. Very
thinly slice into half moon shapes. Drain and rinse the
@chickpeas{1%400g can}. Separate the leaves from the stalks of the
@coriander{1/2%bunch} and roughly chop both.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-low heat and add the
@ground cumin{3/4%tsp}, @ras-el-Hanout{1.5%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp}. After
~{1%minute}, add your onion and cook for ~{5%minutes} until soft. Add your
coriander stalks and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Season with @salt{}.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}, @tomato puree{1%tbsp} and your boiling
water together with the @vegetable stock pot{1}.

Rinse the @red split lentils{50%g} thoroughly under running water for
~{1%minute}, then add to your soup and simmer for ~{10%minutes}.

Add your chickpeas and half your coriander leaves and cook for another
~{10%minutes}.

Once your soup has thickened, taste for seasoning and add more salt if necessary.

> Patrick adds a bit of Tabasco to his to spice things up!

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high. Cut the @ciabatta{2} in half and toast
on each side under your grill until golden. Drizzle over a little
@olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{}.

Serve your soup in #bowls{} with your remaining coriander sprinkled on top.
Dollop on some @Greek style yoghurt{2%tbsp} and serve with your ciabatta on the
side.